{"kind":"cas-record-v1","metadata":{"entries":[{"origin_package":"github.com/codalotl/codalotl/internal/gocas","target_package":"github.com/codalotl/codalotl/internal/q/cas","identifier":"DB.Store","question":"For callers that need to scan the filesystem under DB.AbsRoot/\u003cnamespace\u003e, what is the on-disk record file JSON shape produced by Store? Specifically, how are the primary JSON payload and AdditionalInfo fields represented, and are record paths exactly \u003cAbsRoot\u003e/\u003cnamespace\u003e/\u003chash[:2]\u003e/\u003chash[2:]\u003e?","answer":"`DB.Store` currently writes one JSON object per record with this wrapper shape:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"kind\": \"cas-record-v1\",\n  \"metadata\": { \"your\": \"payload\" },\n  \"additional_info\": {\n    \"unix_timestamp\": 123,\n    \"paths\": [\"a.go\", \"b.go\"],\n    \"git_clean\": true,\n    \"git_commit\": \"abc123\",\n    \"git_merge_base\": \"def456\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\nImportant details:\n\n- The primary `jsonable` payload is first encoded with `json.Marshal(jsonable)`.\n- That encoded JSON is stored under the top-level `metadata` field as raw JSON, not as a quoted JSON string.\n  - If `jsonable` marshals to an object, `metadata` is an object.\n  - If it marshals to an array/string/number/etc., `metadata` is that JSON value.\n- `additional_info` is optional.\n  - It is omitted entirely if `opts == nil` or if `opts.AdditionalInfo` is all zero values.\n  - If present, it uses the JSON field names from `AdditionalInfo`: `unix_timestamp`, `paths`, `git_clean`, `git_commit`, `git_merge_base`.\n- Every stored record has `\"kind\":\"cas-record-v1\"`.\n\nThe record path implementation is:\n\n```go\nfilepath.Join(db.AbsRoot, namespace, hash[:2], hash[2:])\n```\n\nSo conceptually yes, records are stored at:\n\n```text\n\u003cAbsRoot\u003e/\u003cnamespace\u003e/\u003chash[:2]\u003e/\u003chash[2:]\u003e\n```\n\nwith these caveats:\n\n- It uses `filepath.Join`, so separators are OS-specific and the final path may be cleaned.\n- `namespace` and `hash` are validated to be non-empty and contain no `/` or `\\`.\n- `hash` must be at least 3 characters.\n- `Store` writes a temporary file named like `cas-tmp-*` in the final shard directory before renaming it, so a concurrent filesystem scan could briefly observe temp files. Final records themselves have no extension and are named exactly `hash[2:]` inside the `hash[:2]` directory."}]},"additional_info":{"unix_timestamp":1779149768,"paths":["internal/q/cas/SPEC.md","internal/q/cas/cas.go","internal/q/cas/cas_test.go","internal/q/cas/doc.go"],"git_clean":true,"git_commit":"23d62eadf096eb23a4f15d74e228f5e2420204ea","git_merge_base":"b13e15b5cd06125e6af74eeecf800acf0092764d"}}